    "plan_content": "Here's the complete implementation plan:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: Add `Stepper` Compound Component\n\n### Files to create/modify\n| Action | Path |\n|--------|------|\n| **CREATE** | `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/stepper.tsx` |\n| **CREATE** | `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/examples/stepper-demo.tsx` |\n| **APPEND** | `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/_registry.ts` |\n| **APPEND** | `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/examples/_registry.ts` |\n\nNo existing component files are touched.\n\n---\n\n### `stepper.tsx` Architecture\n\nModeled after `carousel.tsx` using **two-level React context** (no Radix UI needed — pure React + Tailwind):\n\n**Context layer 1 — `StepperContext`** (root): shares `activeStep` + `orientation` with all descendants.\n\n**Context layer 2 — `StepperItemContext`** (per-item): shares `step` + derived `state: \"completed\" | \"active\" | \"pending\"` with trigger/separator/title/description.\n\n**Seven exports:**\n- `Stepper` — provider root, renders `<div data-slot=\"stepper\" data-orientation={...}>` with `flex-row` or `flex-col`\n- `StepperItem` — computes `state` from context (`step < activeStep` → completed, `=== activeStep` → active, else pending), sets `data-state` attribute\n- `StepperTrigger` — `<button>` showing step number (or custom `children`); styled via **`cva`** with 3 state variants (completed = filled primary, active = outlined primary, pending = muted outline)\n- `StepperTitle` — `<p data-slot=\"stepper-title\">` for label text\n- `StepperDescription` — `<p data-slot=\"stepper-description\">` for sub-label\n- `StepperSeparator` — `<div>` line; reads orientation from `useStepper()` and state from `useStepperItem()`; uses `data-[state=completed]:bg-primary` CSS selector to highlight when the parent step is passed\n- `StepperContent` — returns `null` unless `step === activeStep`; swapping content panel\n\n**`cva` definition:**\n```ts\nconst stepperTriggerVariants = cva(\"inline-flex size-8 rounded-full border-2 ...\", {\n  variants: {\n    state: {\n      completed: \"border-primary bg-primary text-primary-foreground\",\n      active:    \"border-primary bg-background text-primary\",\n      pending:   \"border-muted-foreground/30 bg-background text-muted-foreground\",\n    },\n  },\n  defaultVariants: { state: \"pending\" },\n})\n```\n\n---\n\n### `stepper-demo.tsx`\n\n- `\"use client\"` + `React.useState(1)` for `activeStep`\n- 3 steps: **Account → Profile → Complete**, each with `StepperTrigger` (clickable to jump), `StepperTitle`, `StepperDescription`, and `StepperSeparator` (except last step)\n- `StepperContent` panels swap in/out as `activeStep` changes\n- \"Previous\" / \"Next\" `Button` components for linear nav with disabled states at boundaries\n\n---\n\n### Registry entries\n\n**`ui/_registry.ts`** — no npm dependencies (pure React/Tailwind):\n```ts\n{ name: \"stepper\", type: \"registry:ui\", files: [{ path: \"ui/stepper.tsx\", type: \"registry:ui\" }] }\n```\n\n**`examples/_registry.ts`** — depends on both `stepper` and `button`:\n```ts\n{ name: \"stepper-demo\", type: \"registry:example\", registryDependencies: [\"stepper\", \"button\"], files: [...] }\n```\n\nBoth entries inserted in alphabetical order.",
